               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18461123-name-1035" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18461123-name-1035" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18461123-name-1035" type="surname" value="CHADDOCK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18461123-name-1035" type="given" value="JOSEPH EDWARD"></interp>JOSEPH EDWARD CHADDOCK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a baker's boy, and carry bread about for Mr. Savory, of the New Cut, Lambeth. On Saturday, 7th of Nov, I met the prisoner and another boy—they offered to help me to. carry the bread—I had received my wages just before that, a sixpence and seventeen groats—they asked whether my master paid me, or paid my mother—I said he paid me—we got on to Bridge-walk, Lambeth, and the prisoner said, "I will lay you sixpence I will put you down in wrestling"—I said, "No, I shall lose my money"—he then threw me down and got on me—when I got up, my money was gone and my trowsers unbuttoned—I told him he had it—he ran away, and I did not see him any more till he was taken on Sunday morning—I am sure he is the person—I felt his hand about me, but I did not feel it in my pocket—no one else could have taken the money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi> There was a man came by.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18461123-name-1036" type="witnessName">
